article.headline: Arkansas St. 54, Middle Tennessee 51
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Adrian Banks and Isaac Wells combined for 33 points as Arkansas State held off Middle Tennessee State 54-51 on Wednesday night. The Indians (10-10, 5-3 Sun Belt Conference) led most of the second half but Middle Tennessee (8-10, 4-4) stayed close with reserve Desmond Yates hitting for 23 points. Middle Tennessee's last lead was 25-24 with 18:56 left on a layup by Theryn Hudson. A 3-pointer by Wells gave the Indians their biggest lead, 49-42, with 5:51 left. The Blue Raiders got to within 53-51 with 12 seconds left on a basket by Yates, but Banks made a free throw with 9 seconds left for the final margin. Banks finished with 17 points and Wells had 16 and a game-high seven rebounds. Yates was the only player in double figures for Middle Tennessee, which had won four of its last five games. The Indians shot 47.6 percent, including 8-of-14 3-pointers. Middle Tennessee hit 37 percent, and the Blue Raiders' Kevin Kanaskie was just 1-of-13 from the floor.
